data.title: general paresis of the insane
data.text:
English

[edit]

Alternative forms

[edit]

general paresis (short form), GPI (initialism)

Noun

[edit]

general paresis of the insane (uncountable)

(pathology) A neuropsychiatric disorder caused by late-stage syphilis, and characterized by fatigue, headaches, insomnia, personality changes, delusions, etc.

Synonyms

[edit]

(neuropsychiatric disorder caused by syphilis): general paralysis of the insane, paralytic dementia

Translations

[edit]

neuropsychiatric disorder caused by syphilis
